<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-07-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="371" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d371">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2756</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Berlin</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LJC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-07-26">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1916</hi>
                                    </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received July 27, 11.10 a.
                                        m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>245. <hi rend="italic">Imperial Gazette</hi> published last evening
                                amendment to prize ordinance of September 30, 1909, which went into
                                effect July 22 last. New regulations which are officially stated
                                nature reprisal for position Great Britain and Allies on London
                                Declaration, contain new lists absolute and relative contraband, new
                                free list, and commentaries showing German position on points of
                                controversy. Official copies amendment have been forwarded
                                Department in to-day’s mail.<note n="1" xml:id="d371fn1">Not
                                    printed.</note> Lists are long but will be cabled if
                                desired.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LJC1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>